            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="duk.00175.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <div1 type="notes">
            <head type="main-derived"><handShift new="#h1"/>Diderot (Dennis Diderot)</head>
            <ab>1713&#8211;1784 (71 years)</ab>
            <ab>His father a cutler, good man&#8212;mother also
            good</ab>
            <ab>D. educated well by the Jesuits.</ab>
            <ab>Came to Paris a young man&#8212;lived ten
            years a loafer, a rascal, a literary
            hack</ab>
            <ab>Emerged by degrees&#8212;is the back‑bone and
            brain of the French Encyclopoedia</ab>
            <ab>(The Enc. was some years (12, 16, or 20) in
            being finished.)</ab>
            <ab>Diderot was befriended by the Russian
            Empress Catherine&#8212;she gave him
            £3000.</ab>
            <ab>It is said of him that he had the
            most encyclopoedical head ever
            in the world, and was a most
            superb talker.</ab>
            <ab>Diderot with his <hi rend="underline">mouth</hi> <hi rend="underline">of gold</hi>&#8212;</ab>
            </div1>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="duk.00175.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
